1
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,927
This is solid evidence for the case.

2
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:55,889
The girl in that video
is Faye Figueroa.

3
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:57,557
She's the missing student.

4
00:00:58,266 --> 00:01:01,519
I’ll learn a lot more if I go with you.

5
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:04,272
I need to learn from the best.

6
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:06,356
Why?

7
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:08,966
Do you think I had something to do
with what happened to her?

8
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:11,988
Let's meet at 4:30 p.m.
at the abandoned building.

9
00:01:36,673 --> 00:01:38,273
Is this what you’re looking for, Nestor?

10
00:01:38,784 --> 00:01:41,453
It’s Hector, Loki. Not Nestor!

11
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:43,895
Do you think this is enough, huh?

12
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:48,650
To pin the crime
you’re accusing me of on me?

13
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:57,199
What?

14
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:00,578
Should we tell Loki now?

15
00:02:01,519 --> 00:02:03,604
Yes. He needs to know.

16
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,986
Hello! Is this Mr. Loki Mendez?

17
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:34,462
Yes, doc.

18
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:36,990
Doctor’s appointment process here
is really, really fast, huh?

19
00:02:37,448 --> 00:02:39,658
Yes, Mr. Mendez. I am Dr. Aquino.

20
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:41,411
What would you like
to consult about today?

21
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:44,873
Well, few days ago
I got punched in the face.

22
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,624
And as you can see,

23
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:50,670
a few bruises around the nose
and around my eyes.

24
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:52,130
Okay.

25
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:56,759
It seems like your soft tissue injury
and bruises are recovering.

26
00:02:57,051 --> 00:03:00,345
For now, just continue applying
cold compress to the affected area

27
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:03,099
for ten to 15 minutes,
three to four times a day.

28
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:05,727
If possible, avoid any heavy activity
for now, okay?

29
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:09,689
You can take a pain reliever
like paracetamol if it hurts.

30
00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:10,940
Is that clear?

31
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:12,859
Yes, doc. Got it!

32
00:03:12,942 --> 00:03:15,903
Okay. I’ll be waiting
for your follow-up checkup, huh?

33
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:17,197
Just book through the app, okay?

34
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:18,405
Thank you, doc!

35
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:20,532
Okay! I’ll go ahead, Mr. Loki Mendez.

36
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,911
I will send you your med cert
and e-prescription.

37
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:24,078
Noted, doc.

38
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:25,371
Okay. Bye!

39
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,179
OMG!

40
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:44,807
Loki, you look really bad.

41
00:03:45,516 --> 00:03:47,810
Was Lori’s punch that strong?

42
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:51,064
Oh, my gosh.

43
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:53,816
Loki.

44
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:58,363
Well, was it worth it?

45
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:02,659
Yes, Hector got caught,
but you got hurt too.

46
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:09,916
The most important thing
is that Hector is arrested.

47
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:14,170
I hope this is the last time you do this.

48
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:16,339
I don’t like seeing you in this shape.

49
00:04:18,466 --> 00:04:19,592
By the way...

50
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:23,930
so, we checked Bastien’s call logs.

51
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:28,518
And there were a couple of matches
for Jamie’s number combinations.

52
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:31,688
So what, should we call the number?

53
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:35,942
No. It’s too early to do that.

54
00:04:36,901 --> 00:04:38,736
Let’s not show our aces yet.

55
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:42,323
You know what,
it’s better to wait for the right moment

56
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:44,409
before we put our cards on the table.

57
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:46,744
But when, Loki?

58
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:50,248
Killings have been happening
one after another here at our school.

59
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:53,501
We need to catch whoever
this Moriarty is.

60
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:58,339
When I dial that number,

61
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,675
I wanna see that person answer my call,

62
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:05,138
so I can confirm
whether he’s Moriarty or not.

63
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:09,309
Texting or calling him now
is an idiotic move.

64
00:05:09,934 --> 00:05:13,146
Let’s standby
and wait for a window of opportunity.

65
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:16,315
Alright.

66
00:05:19,527 --> 00:05:21,236
Oh, why is this back?

67
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,488
This website should be banned for life.

68
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:24,324
Let’s report it again

69
00:05:24,325 --> 00:05:26,450
so it won’t spread fake news anymore.

70
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:28,244
No to fake news peddlers!

71
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:29,953
This is just for content, right?

72
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:32,582
Looks like they just want
to make mystery-crime stories.

73
00:05:34,542 --> 00:05:35,585
Deception...

74
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:39,922
Can deception ever justify
the pursuit of truth?

75
00:05:40,673 --> 00:05:42,716
The tragedy of Hector and Faye

76
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:44,176
reminds us that.

77
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:47,179
Every lie, no matter how well-intentioned,

78
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,765
carries consequences.

79
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:52,309
It wounds trust, blurs morality,

80
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:55,313
and, in Faye’s case, can turn fatal.

81
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:02,111
And yet her death is not the end.

82
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:06,074
Behind this crime
lies another layer of deception,

83
00:06:06,407 --> 00:06:09,577
one so deep that death
continues to follow in its wake...

84
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,834
Through Moriarty’s lies,
identities dissolve.

85
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:18,711
Leaving us to ask...

86
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:21,089
are we truly safe?

87
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:24,258
Or are we also deceiving ourselves?

88
00:06:27,595 --> 00:06:30,972
Or perhaps, the silence, the secrecy,

89
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:34,352
and the calculated lies
suggest something more unsettling,

90
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:36,312
that in our pursuit of safety,

91
00:06:37,146 --> 00:06:40,233
we may be doing the very things
that place us in danger.

92
00:06:45,029 --> 00:06:48,825
Sometimes, the greatest threat
is not the enemy we see,

93
00:06:49,575 --> 00:06:51,994
but the deception we allow to exist.

94
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:05,758
So, have you seen Jamie?

95
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,927
She told me that she’ll be late.

96
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:12,265
By the way, do you know what X is?

97
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:13,473
X?

98
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:18,479
There are three X’s
at the end of Jamie’s message.

99
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:23,733
Well, If I’m not mistaken,

100
00:07:23,734 --> 00:07:26,737
X is usually an expression of affection.

101
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:29,866
Are you familiar with XOXO?

102
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:33,326
Let’s put it this way,

103
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:37,206
do you remember the Madonna Barcelon case?

104
00:07:37,373 --> 00:07:41,294
When she gave us those signed photos
that were signed with XOXO?

105
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:46,423
Well, X usually represents kiss

106
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:48,759
and O represents hug.

107
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:52,680
X can also mean target
or X marks the spot.

108
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,850
Why would she send me three kisses?

109
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:57,767
I don’t know.

110
00:07:58,227 --> 00:08:01,230
Maybe she wants to kiss you again.

111
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,494
Brace yourself, Lorelei.

112
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:16,996
The apocalypse is about to begin.

113
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:23,377
♪ Shadows. ♪

114
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:27,006
♪ In the dark are crawling. ♪

115
00:08:27,691 --> 00:08:31,736
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪

116
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:35,306
♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪

117
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:39,851
♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪

118
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:43,021
♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪

119
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:45,982
♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪

120
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:50,488
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory. ♪

121
00:08:51,871 --> 00:08:53,998
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

122
00:08:55,243 --> 00:08:57,620
♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪

123
00:08:58,704 --> 00:09:02,375
♪ For this world ♪

124
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,669
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

125
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:08,130
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

126
00:09:09,131 --> 00:09:11,259
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

127
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:16,097
♪ For this world ♪

128
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:19,349
is not what you imagined.

129
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:24,188
Heed the warnings.

130
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:29,402
The apocalypse is upon us.

131
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,488
Yeah, the apocalypse.

132
00:09:32,613 --> 00:09:38,619
The apocalypse has been informed
that there are three of you now?

133
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:42,831
Maggie also told me

134
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:46,627
you have a new recruit
who looks just like your old friend.

135
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:50,089
I assume this is not a social visit.

136
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:53,259
Shall we cut to the chase,
why are you here?

137
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:56,012
Isn’t obvious?

138
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:59,890
I just wanted to say hello
to my younger brother.

139
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:01,891
Really?

140
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:05,605
You wouldn't go out of your way
just to visit and say hi.

141
00:10:06,731 --> 00:10:07,731
Very well.

142
00:10:10,526 --> 00:10:12,945
I will no longer disturb you.

143
00:10:13,654 --> 00:10:16,532
The student council needs
your club’s assistance.

144
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:18,618
What kind of assistance?

145
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:20,911
Is it to dominate the world?

146
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:25,291
Or eliminate the threats
to your secret empire.

147
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:27,168
If that’s not the answer,

148
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:29,503
I don’t wanna be a part of it.

149
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:31,631
See, that’s the thing.

150
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:36,302
Loki, I don’t think
you can refuse my request.

151
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:38,637
Thirty minutes ago,

152
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:41,223
a card was delivered
to the student council’s office.

153
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:45,311
And of course,
as our campus detective club...

154
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,730
if not you, who else?

155
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:49,522
Right?

156
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,067
So?

157
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:55,029
And why do you think
we’ll accommodate your request?

158
00:10:57,073 --> 00:11:00,284
This card came
from a very close friend of yours.

159
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:04,121
Looks like he’s tired of hiding
in his shadow.

160
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,041
Do you mind?

161
00:11:15,091 --> 00:11:16,091
M.

162
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:18,302
Moriarty.

163
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:35,361
We’re planning to...

164
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:38,781
send that card to our campus police.

165
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:41,492
Have them check
if there’s any fingerprints on it.

166
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:43,410
You’re a fool if you think Moriarty

167
00:11:43,411 --> 00:11:46,914
or whoever wrote this letter
would leave any traces.

168
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:50,835
He’s far too meticulous
to leave breadcrumbs

169
00:11:51,293 --> 00:11:54,004
for us to pick up and follow.

170
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:57,465
Nevertheless, the student council
believes that this matter

171
00:11:57,466 --> 00:12:01,178
should be taken seriously
and definitely not lightly.

172
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:04,098
You know, next time,

173
00:12:04,598 --> 00:12:07,393
it might be the name of the next target,

174
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:10,312
or worst could be

175
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:14,107
the name of the next location
where a bomb could be planted,

176
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:16,193
I don’t know,
somewhere random in the school.

177
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:19,697
Why don’t you refer this case
to the student execom?

178
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:22,658
Weren’t they also investigating
the Moriarty case?

179
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:25,327
They are busy at the moment.

180
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:28,873
With the little stunt
that you pulled the other day.

181
00:12:29,331 --> 00:12:31,709
And Maggie...

182
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:33,710
Yeah, she wasn’t exactly happy

183
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:36,005
about the fact
that you were like sniffing around.

184
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:39,132
Do you realize, Loki,

185
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,301
that you just cut loose the thread

186
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:45,848
that could have led them
to the mystery man?

187
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,434
Good job.

188
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:50,728
Good job with that one.

189
00:12:51,395 --> 00:12:53,773
Some sacrifices have to be made.

190
00:12:54,565 --> 00:12:58,485
And they’re nowhere closer
to Moriarty than we are.

191
00:12:58,486 --> 00:12:59,486
Oh, yeah?

192
00:13:00,321 --> 00:13:01,781
Then what do you mean by that?

193
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:03,699
You don't need to know.

194
00:13:05,242 --> 00:13:07,036
You’ve already delivered the message.

195
00:13:09,246 --> 00:13:10,372
Can you leave us now?

196
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:13,584
Your presence is distracting.

197
00:13:14,251 --> 00:13:16,045
We need to concentrate.

198
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:19,173
And If this message threatens someone,

199
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,092
we must act quickly.

200
00:13:25,012 --> 00:13:29,391
Alright. Well, let us know
once you have cracked that code.

201
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:31,476
It’s important for the student council

202
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:33,354
to know the progress that is happening.

203
00:13:34,104 --> 00:13:35,104
Alright!

204
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:49,370
You rarely see the Student Council
Vice President visit a club.

205
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,915
The fact that he delivered
the card himself

206
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:55,251
shows how serious their concern is.

207
00:13:56,418 --> 00:13:57,837
He could’ve sent someone else,

208
00:13:58,796 --> 00:13:59,797
but he didn’t.

209
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:02,800
Then let’s start cracking it!

210
00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:06,470
We don’t have time to waste.

211
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:09,348
If someone’s life is at stake,

212
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:12,560
then we should decode this even faster.

213
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:19,441
Simple substitution does not work.

214
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:22,069
Why don’t you try the Polybius square?

215
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:25,406
There are two single digit numbers here.

216
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:29,785
And the Polybius Square
only works with two-digit numbers.

217
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,956
What if this is like
the double code you made?

218
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:37,626
After getting the first set of letters,

219
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:42,756
what if we wrote down the letters
that precede them.

220
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:46,176
Take one step back, remember?

221
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:50,806
Might be worth a try.

222
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:19,877
If Moriarty chose a cipher
that I’m not aware of,

223
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:23,464
he got me in this one.

224
00:15:26,008 --> 00:15:27,008
Listen...

225
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:31,972
maybe it’s not one step back,

226
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:35,893
but one or two steps forward?

227
00:15:51,158 --> 00:15:52,660
Every code has a pattern,

228
00:15:53,994 --> 00:15:55,496
which makes it crackable.

229
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:58,749
Either these numbers are meaningless,

230
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,835
or I’ve overlooked something important.

231
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,213
Let me see.

232
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:11,887
What could
"Greetings from Henry VIII" be for?

233
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:16,058
I doubt they’d include this
if it wasn’t relevant.

234
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,769
Do you know who Henry VIII is?

235
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:24,400
He could be one of the monarchs
of the United Kingdom.

236
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:27,695
It’s sounds like a name
that’s fit for a king.

237
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:28,861
You're right.

238
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:30,405
He was a king.

239
00:16:32,032 --> 00:16:33,367
Henry VIII...

240
00:16:34,576 --> 00:16:36,328
the second Tudor monarch,

241
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:39,415
had six wives seeking a son

242
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:43,210
but did not contribute much
to the cryptography.

243
00:16:43,676 --> 00:16:44,760
Again,

244
00:16:45,004 --> 00:16:48,048
why would Moriarty include this
if it wasn’t relevant?

245
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:50,299
My deduction is

246
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:54,304
is that maybe Henry VIII holds the clue
to cracking this code.

247
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:57,599
Interesting insight, Lorelei.

248
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:02,771
There has to be something
with that fat British monarch.

249
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:06,483
Or what if eight...

250
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:14,867
Sorry but we’re currently busy
at the moment.

251
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:19,955
I just wanted to ask
if Jamie passed by here.

252
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:22,041
Or do you know where she went?

253
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:24,126
She hasn’t come here yet.

254
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:25,878
She said that she’ll be late.

255
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:28,046
Because she attended class this morning,

256
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:31,091
then left the classroom
saying she had somewhere to go.

257
00:17:32,801 --> 00:17:37,222
Our first class already started,
and she still hasn’t come back.

258
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:44,146
Didn’t Jamie tell you she’d be late
getting to the clubroom?

259
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:46,774
But she failed to attend
her morning classes.

260
00:17:47,649 --> 00:17:48,984
Therefore...

261
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,572
Good morning, Loki.

262
00:17:54,573 --> 00:17:55,948
Sorry, I’m going to be late.

263
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:57,742
I still have something I need to finish.

264
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:00,661
I’ll catch up once we’re done.
Is that okay? Thank you!

265
00:18:00,662 --> 00:18:02,498
If Jamie didn’t go to class,

266
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:04,582
it means,

267
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:06,959
she either cut classes

268
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:09,546
and just pretended she was going to class.

269
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:14,635
Or someone else
sent you that text message, Loki.

270
00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:18,889
It looks like you’re right
about the meaning of letter X.

271
00:18:19,807 --> 00:18:21,809
Considering the recent news,

272
00:18:22,309 --> 00:18:24,478
it’s probably meant to mark the target.

273
00:18:25,395 --> 00:18:26,897
And in this case,

274
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:29,191
it’s our very own...

275
00:18:30,192 --> 00:18:31,568
Jamie Santiago.

276
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:42,412
I think she’s still alive.

277
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,290
The question is...

278
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:47,835
until when?

279
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:51,546
Moriarty’s giving us a chance
to find her location

280
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:53,215
until he gets bored.

281
00:18:56,093 --> 00:18:57,344
Unfortunately...

282
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,389
we still have no idea
on how we can crack this code.

283
00:19:01,014 --> 00:19:03,934
You know, instead of just sitting there,

284
00:19:04,017 --> 00:19:05,894
help me deal with this.

285
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:09,731
After hearing that news,

286
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:13,110
I can’t give my full attention
to the sequence of numbers.

287
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,367
I hate this feeling!

288
00:19:21,368 --> 00:19:23,871
You know, we should ask Luthor for help.

289
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:24,912
No.

290
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:27,915
My God... Loki, we need to find Jamie!

291
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:28,916
Or else...

292
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:33,838
Look, there’s nothing wrong
with asking for help

293
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,340
if it’s for her.

294
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:38,719
For once, my God,
can you just please put aside your pride?

295
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:40,929
For the sake of others.

296
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:06,662
Our next agenda

297
00:20:06,663 --> 00:20:08,999
is the budget for the school year.

298
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Alright.

299
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:17,423
We are currently in
the middle of a meeting.

300
00:20:17,424 --> 00:20:20,092
So I would gladly appreciate

301
00:20:20,093 --> 00:20:23,972
that you would’ve at least warned me
before you would barge in.

302
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:30,062
Apologies for interrupting
your world-domination discussion.

303
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:32,856
The vice president requested our help,

304
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:35,067
and we agreed.

305
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:38,862
Now we urgently need your resources.

306
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:41,865
Have you crack the code?

307
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:44,283
Not yet.

308
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:46,578
But we know who the target is.

309
00:20:48,455 --> 00:20:51,625
Our club’s newest member is missing.

310
00:20:52,292 --> 00:20:54,544
We fear that she’s been abducted.

311
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:57,673
The code you left
could lead us to her location.

312
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:01,510
Unfortunately, we can’t crack the code.

313
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:04,137
So I've decided to use an alternative.

314
00:21:04,429 --> 00:21:05,639
Okay. Which is?

315
00:21:10,143 --> 00:21:13,271
I want you to command
all students at your disposal

316
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:16,316
to search every room in this building.

317
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:18,986
Maybe she was just hidden
here on campus.

318
00:21:19,486 --> 00:21:21,738
Huh? It can’t just happen like that
all of a sudden.

319
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:23,991
That still has to be approved
by the admin.

320
00:21:24,408 --> 00:21:25,408
No.

321
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:29,538
We don’t have the luxury of time
to secure permission from the admin.

322
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:35,752
Yes. I can read your lip movements.

323
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:39,673
And if you want to prevent
another victim of Moriarty,

324
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:43,302
I suggest you stop muttering

325
00:21:43,885 --> 00:21:45,595
and give us the urgent help we need.

326
00:21:47,889 --> 00:21:48,889
Very well.

327
00:21:49,641 --> 00:21:52,436
Jessica, please,
do you mind calling Maggie?

328
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:54,855
Tell her it’s an urgent matter.

329
00:21:55,063 --> 00:21:56,481
- Okay.
- Thank you.

330
00:22:05,532 --> 00:22:07,659
What the hell are you doing here?

331
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:09,828
Maggie, thank you for coming.

332
00:22:10,078 --> 00:22:13,414
As you can see, the Q.E.D. Club
is requesting for manpower

333
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:16,293
for the search
of their missing club member.

334
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,044
I guess we have no other choice

335
00:22:18,045 --> 00:22:20,171
than to mobilize
all the available members

336
00:22:20,172 --> 00:22:21,965
of the student executive committee.

337
00:22:23,050 --> 00:22:25,844
So the magnet of tragedies strikes again.

338
00:22:26,553 --> 00:22:29,264
I knew it, you’re really unlucky.

339
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:33,393
You had a taste of it, right, Lorelei?

340
00:22:34,394 --> 00:22:36,604
If the student council commands it,

341
00:22:36,605 --> 00:22:38,523
then the execom shall oblige.

342
00:22:39,149 --> 00:22:40,984
Let’s pray that she’s still alive,

343
00:22:41,401 --> 00:22:44,571
'cause if not,
her blood is on your hands.

344
00:22:49,451 --> 00:22:51,036
Thank you, Maggie.

345
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:54,539
Don’t thank me.
I’m not doing this for you.

346
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:57,834
And stop calling me Maggie.

347
00:23:01,004 --> 00:23:02,296
Now if you’ll excuse us,

348
00:23:02,297 --> 00:23:05,217
I need to make the same request
to my contact in the campus police.

349
00:23:12,265 --> 00:23:13,558
We’re leaving now.

350
00:23:14,142 --> 00:23:15,142
Thank you.

351
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:18,145
Hello, Chief.

352
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:20,816
Yes. I’m doing fine. Thank you for asking.

353
00:23:21,942 --> 00:23:22,942
I need your help.

354
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:25,695
One of our club members is missing.

355
00:23:26,863 --> 00:23:30,200
Can you and your men
conduct a search in the campus?

356
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:32,202
I’ll send you her photo.

357
00:23:34,830 --> 00:23:36,248
So what do we do next?

358
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:40,794
While the execom and campus police
are searching the school buildings,

359
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:43,588
let’s try cracking the code again.

360
00:23:57,436 --> 00:23:58,727
You mentioned that Henry VIII

361
00:23:58,728 --> 00:24:00,730
might be the clue to decoding
this sequence?

362
00:24:01,064 --> 00:24:02,107
Yes. That’s right.

363
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:16,246
Henry VIII. What’s your deal?

364
00:24:16,872 --> 00:24:18,664
Why were you mentioned
in the Moriarty card

365
00:24:18,665 --> 00:24:21,334
when you haven’t contributed anything
to cryptography?

366
00:24:23,086 --> 00:24:24,546
Maybe the answer isn’t in Henry,

367
00:24:25,172 --> 00:24:26,798
maybe it’s in VIII?

368
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:32,637
What’s with eight?

369
00:24:34,890 --> 00:24:37,934
In the Bible,
eight represents a new beginning.

370
00:24:38,727 --> 00:24:42,147
In chemistry,
eight is the atomic number of oxygen.

371
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:46,902
In computer tech,
eight bits are equivalent to one byte.

372
00:24:47,694 --> 00:24:50,238
In Chinese and other Asian cultures,

373
00:24:50,739 --> 00:24:52,866
eight is considered to be a lucky number.

374
00:24:53,408 --> 00:24:54,534
Sideways,

375
00:24:55,202 --> 00:24:57,204
eight looks like the infinity symbol.

376
00:24:59,039 --> 00:25:00,332
What am I missing?

377
00:25:01,124 --> 00:25:02,124
Wait.

378
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:05,754
I feel like I heard something recently
that’s connected to the number eight.

379
00:25:06,129 --> 00:25:07,839
What was it about again?

380
00:25:08,381 --> 00:25:10,091
I think we studied it before.

381
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:12,594
That’s because we have ten fingers.

382
00:25:12,636 --> 00:25:14,804
But what if we have eight?

383
00:25:15,764 --> 00:25:17,932
We count using digits 0 to 7,

384
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:20,143
then we go to 10 to 17.

385
00:25:21,269 --> 00:25:25,398
And that is called octal counting
or base eight.

386
00:25:25,649 --> 00:25:26,733
Base eight!

387
00:25:27,859 --> 00:25:28,859
What?

388
00:25:29,277 --> 00:25:30,820
Do you know what base eight is?

389
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:33,989
Is that some kind of game or something?

390
00:25:33,990 --> 00:25:36,117
No! No! No!
It’s a way of counting numbers.

391
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:39,704
Our professor in Math 100 taught us this.

392
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:43,290
Math professor, Jim Morayta?

393
00:25:43,291 --> 00:25:44,209
Yes! That’s right.

394
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:47,294
So I think your substitution is correct,

395
00:25:47,295 --> 00:25:51,258
but you shouldn’t have used traditional
decimal counting as the reference.

396
00:25:51,424 --> 00:25:53,093
Don’t you have this kind of subject?

397
00:25:53,718 --> 00:25:55,845
- Come on. Show me.
- Okay.

398
00:25:56,263 --> 00:25:57,513
This is how it goes.

399
00:25:57,514 --> 00:25:59,139
So now,

400
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:02,352
we need to match
the letters with the numbers.

401
00:26:02,936 --> 00:26:04,020
Hand me a pen.

402
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:09,818
So, 11 stands for J,

403
00:26:10,235 --> 00:26:12,112
0 stands for A,

404
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:15,323
14 stands for M,

405
00:26:16,116 --> 00:26:18,159
10 stands for I,

406
00:26:18,743 --> 00:26:20,495
4 stands for E

407
00:26:21,121 --> 00:26:23,957
10 stands for I.

408
00:26:24,749 --> 00:26:25,917
What does that mean?

409
00:26:30,589 --> 00:26:31,923
Jamie in props room.

410
00:26:39,306 --> 00:26:40,307
Have you found her?

411
00:26:40,348 --> 00:26:41,516
We haven’t.

412
00:26:41,558 --> 00:26:44,519
They’ve already searched every room
on campus, but there’s nothing.

413
00:26:44,644 --> 00:26:46,646
No. I’m right.

414
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:49,566
Lorelei cracked the code
just a few minutes ago.

415
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:51,109
We already know where she is.

416
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:52,652
Have you checked the props room?

417
00:26:53,111 --> 00:26:54,613
No, not yet.

418
00:27:00,952 --> 00:27:03,455
We have to see for ourselves
if Jamie’s really not there.

419
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:05,332
Let’s go.

420
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:22,098
Maybe she's in a hidden compartment.

421
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:29,647
Jamie.

422
00:27:31,941 --> 00:27:32,941
Try that.

423
00:27:38,281 --> 00:27:39,282
Help me out here.

424
00:27:44,829 --> 00:27:45,829
Look.

425
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:48,082
What’s that?

426
00:27:50,085 --> 00:27:51,085
Look.

427
00:27:51,252 --> 00:27:55,006
Moriarty is planning to kill Jamie
using carbon monoxide poisoning.

428
00:27:55,382 --> 00:27:57,800
And as long as this room is airtight,

429
00:27:57,801 --> 00:28:00,095
and the victim is unconscious
or restrained,

430
00:28:00,595 --> 00:28:04,557
she would succumb
in a matter of seconds or minutes.

431
00:28:07,394 --> 00:28:08,936
But the question still is,

432
00:28:08,937 --> 00:28:10,480
where exactly is she?

433
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:15,401
Jamie’s in here!

434
00:28:31,584 --> 00:28:32,544
- Jamie!
- Jamie!

435
00:28:32,545 --> 00:28:33,669
Jamie! Jamie!

436
00:28:33,670 --> 00:28:34,670
Oh, my God.

437
00:28:34,879 --> 00:28:36,381
Loki! She’s bleeding!

438
00:28:42,095 --> 00:28:43,095
Jamie.

439
00:28:44,264 --> 00:28:45,098
Jamie.

440
00:28:45,099 --> 00:28:46,599
- Loki, she’s bleeding!
- Jamie!

441
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:49,102
Jamie.

442
00:28:49,394 --> 00:28:50,811
God. She's okay.

443
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:53,273
- Oh, my God. Help!
- Jamie. Help!

444
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:54,690
Help!

445
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:57,192
- We need a medic!
- They found her!

446
00:28:57,193 --> 00:28:57,861
- Help!
- Help!

447
00:28:57,861 --> 00:28:58,861
They found her!

448
00:28:59,028 --> 00:29:00,237
They're here!

449
00:29:00,238 --> 00:29:01,632
- Someone call a medic.
- Is she okay?

450
00:29:01,656 --> 00:29:02,782
How is she?

451
00:29:04,367 --> 00:29:05,807
- It will be okay, Loki.
- She’s alive!

452
00:29:06,745 --> 00:29:07,745
She's alive.

453
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:08,996
Get some help.

454
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:10,331
Okay. Come on, bro.

455
00:29:24,637 --> 00:29:26,556
Are her parents on their way?

456
00:29:28,808 --> 00:29:31,603
Sadly, Jamie is completely orphaned.

457
00:29:31,895 --> 00:29:35,272
The one who answered my call earlier
was the caretaker of the house.

458
00:29:35,273 --> 00:29:37,901
But they’re on their way here
to pick her up.

459
00:29:47,994 --> 00:29:49,913
Now that Jamie’s out of harm’s way,

460
00:29:50,705 --> 00:29:53,166
it’s time for us
to meet face to face with Moriarty.

461
00:29:54,876 --> 00:29:59,589
Are you going to text or call the number
we got from Officer Montreal?

462
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:01,174
You have his number, right?

463
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:03,675
I didn’t save it in my contacts.

464
00:30:03,676 --> 00:30:06,930
I’m not talking about the number
the officer gave you.

465
00:30:07,889 --> 00:30:08,765
I’m talking about the number

466
00:30:08,766 --> 00:30:11,559
that he would probably give
to his students.

467
00:30:12,602 --> 00:30:14,144
Sorry, I don’t follow.

468
00:30:14,145 --> 00:30:18,023
I don’t understand what,
or who, you’re referring to.

469
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:20,902
I want you to set up a meeting
at 4 p.m. tomorrow

470
00:30:20,944 --> 00:30:22,570
with Professor Jim Morayta,

471
00:30:23,154 --> 00:30:24,739
your Math 100 professor.

472
00:30:25,865 --> 00:30:26,865
No more questions.

473
00:30:27,575 --> 00:30:28,618
Just do it.

474
00:30:29,244 --> 00:30:30,244
Wait.

475
00:30:30,537 --> 00:30:32,789
Do you think he has anything
to do with this?

476
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:37,752
We’ll find out once we talk to him.

477
00:30:38,878 --> 00:30:39,963
Really, Loki?

478
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:42,339
Why are you so sure
it's Professor Morayta

479
00:30:42,340 --> 00:30:43,633
that you're accusing him?

480
00:30:48,179 --> 00:30:49,179
Look.

481
00:30:50,014 --> 00:30:51,516
I get it, okay?

482
00:30:52,559 --> 00:30:54,185
I want to catch Moriarty too.

483
00:30:54,435 --> 00:30:57,021
But you're not sure
it's Professor Morayta.

484
00:30:57,313 --> 00:30:59,649
Fine, let's talk to him tomorrow.

485
00:31:00,775 --> 00:31:01,815
Let’s just do it this way.

486
00:31:02,235 --> 00:31:03,945
- I’ll email him first...
- No need.

487
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:06,905
I’ve decided.

488
00:31:07,782 --> 00:31:10,034
I’ll talk to Professor Morayta myself.

489
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:12,953
Why?

490
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:15,290
Because starting today…

491
00:31:17,333 --> 00:31:20,128
I want you and Jamie…

492
00:31:21,588 --> 00:31:22,964
to quit the Q.E.D. Club.

493
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:24,715
Huh?

494
00:31:26,301 --> 00:31:27,510
This is for your own good.

495
00:31:29,220 --> 00:31:31,014
So you won’t get dragged
into danger either.

496
00:31:32,432 --> 00:31:35,018
No! I’m not doing that, Loki!

497
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:38,770
You know, you’re the one
who convinced me to join this club,

498
00:31:38,771 --> 00:31:40,273
and now you want me to quit?

499
00:31:41,316 --> 00:31:43,818
You don’t know
what the Q.E.D. Club means to me.

500
00:31:45,445 --> 00:31:47,488
This is the only place
I feel like I matter.

501
00:31:49,073 --> 00:31:51,659
It’s the only place
where my actions truly matter.

502
00:31:52,869 --> 00:31:54,578
And I’m able to help people

503
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:56,331
by bringing bad people to justice!

504
00:31:56,456 --> 00:31:58,582
And I’m able to use my talent in writing,

505
00:31:58,583 --> 00:32:00,627
to write about the stories of these cases.

506
00:32:01,169 --> 00:32:04,213
So you can’t just get me out
of this club that easily!

507
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:06,215
So, I’m sorry!

508
00:32:06,424 --> 00:32:08,468
But no matter what you say,

509
00:32:08,718 --> 00:32:12,221
I’m going with you tomorrow
when you talk to Professor Morayta.

510
00:32:17,977 --> 00:32:19,394
You’re just causing trouble!

511
00:32:19,395 --> 00:32:22,231
Leave the Q.E.D. Club already. Just quit!

512
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:34,285
I want you and Jamie
to quit the Q.E.D. Club.

513
00:33:15,952 --> 00:33:18,746
Professor James Moriarty.

514
00:33:19,622 --> 00:33:22,916
You may be described
in the Sherlock Holmes novels

515
00:33:22,917 --> 00:33:26,421
as old, pale and thin.

516
00:33:27,296 --> 00:33:30,008
But I know that’s only a mask
for your true nature.

517
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:35,596
That’s why they called you
the Napoleon of Crime, right?

518
00:33:35,972 --> 00:33:38,599
And I know I am one step closer

519
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:41,894
to uncovering your true identity.

520
00:34:30,777 --> 00:34:34,030
Good thing Professor Morayta agreed
to meet with us.

521
00:34:36,783 --> 00:34:40,119
He thinks we’re just going
to consult him about something.

522
00:34:41,454 --> 00:34:45,833
But I still don’t believe your theory
that he’s Moriarty.

523
00:34:50,004 --> 00:34:51,589
Thank you for arranging this meeting.

524
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:55,676
But I have my own game plan
in questioning him.

525
00:34:57,512 --> 00:34:58,512
Trust me.

526
00:34:59,263 --> 00:35:00,263
Wait.

527
00:35:00,681 --> 00:35:04,852
When are you planning to use the number
we got from Officer Montreal?

528
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:08,815
That phone number is our last resort.

529
00:35:09,816 --> 00:35:11,442
If he denies being Moriarty,

530
00:35:12,443 --> 00:35:14,237
I’ll call that number.

531
00:35:15,196 --> 00:35:17,365
And if he answers that call,

532
00:35:19,242 --> 00:35:21,285
that’s the confirmation
we’ve been looking for.

533
00:35:23,371 --> 00:35:25,081
What if your suspicion is wrong?

534
00:35:26,165 --> 00:35:27,625
When am I ever wrong?

535
00:35:32,755 --> 00:35:34,090
Sorry, I’m late.

536
00:35:34,632 --> 00:35:35,632
Professor!

537
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:40,513
We just had a quick meeting
with the student org I handle.

538
00:35:41,222 --> 00:35:43,724
Oh, you’re with Loki. How are you?

539
00:35:47,353 --> 00:35:49,438
Professor, please have a seat.

540
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:53,567
Prof.

541
00:35:54,110 --> 00:35:57,946
Please excuse Loki, he’s just a bit tired.

542
00:35:57,947 --> 00:36:01,742
And he’s also worried about the condition
of one of our club members.

543
00:36:01,784 --> 00:36:03,953
Right. Jamie?

544
00:36:05,204 --> 00:36:06,664
I heard about that incident.

545
00:36:07,081 --> 00:36:08,708
I really hope she gets well soon.

546
00:36:09,375 --> 00:36:12,377
So, Lorelei, what is it that you wanted
to consult to me about

547
00:36:12,378 --> 00:36:13,838
that you couldn’t say on campus?

548
00:36:14,672 --> 00:36:15,672
You can tell me,

549
00:36:16,007 --> 00:36:18,718
and I won’t tell anyone
unless you tell me to.

550
00:36:20,469 --> 00:36:23,096
Actually, Prof, I really have no...

551
00:36:23,097 --> 00:36:24,724
Can you drop your act now, Prof?

552
00:36:27,476 --> 00:36:31,147
There’s no need for you to keep up
with this nice teacher persona.

553
00:36:31,731 --> 00:36:33,274
Take off that mask

554
00:36:34,066 --> 00:36:36,068
and tell us who you really are.

555
00:36:41,365 --> 00:36:42,366
I don’t understand.

556
00:36:42,909 --> 00:36:44,994
What mask and persona
are you talking about?

557
00:36:45,995 --> 00:36:47,205
I don’t follow.

558
00:36:47,288 --> 00:36:49,248
Please! Enlighten me.

559
00:36:50,458 --> 00:36:52,043
Your name is Jim Morayta,

560
00:36:52,585 --> 00:36:55,713
which is a close resemblance
to James Moriarty.

561
00:36:57,590 --> 00:36:59,299
You’re also a mathematics professor

562
00:36:59,300 --> 00:37:01,886
just like the Napoleon of crime.

563
00:37:02,094 --> 00:37:04,180
Everyone on campus respects you.

564
00:37:05,139 --> 00:37:09,310
And a word against you
would be considered slander.

565
00:37:10,770 --> 00:37:12,729
Choosing Moriarty as your alias

566
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:16,067
would be a perfect
and fitting choice, wouldn’t it?

567
00:37:17,902 --> 00:37:20,088
-When I was poisoned with belladonna,
-Loki, please wake up!

568
00:37:20,112 --> 00:37:21,697
- Lorelei said.
- Help!

569
00:37:21,781 --> 00:37:24,533
You were the first to arrive
when she called for help.

570
00:37:24,867 --> 00:37:25,451
Loki!

571
00:37:25,452 --> 00:37:27,410
As if you were on standby

572
00:37:27,411 --> 00:37:30,373
- outside of clubroom waiting on cue.
- Help!

573
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:34,180
I’m not your student, so there’s
no need for you to worry about me.

574
00:37:35,044 --> 00:37:39,048
Then I remembered what one
of Moriarty’s minions revealed to us.

575
00:37:39,715 --> 00:37:43,052
That Moriarty didn’t want me dead.

576
00:37:43,636 --> 00:37:45,679
If I wanted you dead,

577
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,974
I would’ve just killed you outright.

578
00:37:48,641 --> 00:37:50,601
But Moriarty doesn’t want that.

579
00:37:54,730 --> 00:37:56,940
Is it wrong for a teacher

580
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:59,068
to worry about a student?

581
00:37:59,819 --> 00:38:01,654
Back then,
I just happened to pass by.

582
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:04,156
I did my duty as teacher.

583
00:38:04,949 --> 00:38:05,949
Tell me...

584
00:38:06,158 --> 00:38:07,326
what did I do wrong?

585
00:38:15,543 --> 00:38:17,878
In case you’re pretending
you don’t know anything...

586
00:38:20,965 --> 00:38:23,592
this is a code solved in base eight.

587
00:38:25,177 --> 00:38:28,306
And you mentioned that method
of counting in Lorelei’s class.

588
00:38:31,350 --> 00:38:35,186
Who would have thought of integrating
that lesson with a substitution code

589
00:38:35,187 --> 00:38:37,689
except for a math enthusiast?

590
00:38:37,690 --> 00:38:41,777
And that is called octal counting
or base eight.

591
00:38:43,529 --> 00:38:46,699
So just because I taught base eight,

592
00:38:47,491 --> 00:38:49,251
you’re saying I’m the one
who made this code?

593
00:38:50,536 --> 00:38:52,204
Let me remind you, Loki,

594
00:38:52,621 --> 00:38:56,292
octal counting
is not privileged information.

595
00:38:57,126 --> 00:38:59,837
Anyone who’s into math knows this.

596
00:39:00,463 --> 00:39:03,758
And I’m not the only
math teacher in Clark U.

597
00:39:05,134 --> 00:39:07,261
Did you suspect
the other teachers as well?

598
00:39:08,471 --> 00:39:09,471
No?

599
00:39:10,431 --> 00:39:13,309
Now, if you have nothing
to consult, Lorelei, I have to go.

600
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:15,853
Professor, wait!

601
00:39:18,439 --> 00:39:19,439
Prof!

602
00:39:21,442 --> 00:39:22,442
Prof.

603
00:39:23,277 --> 00:39:24,528
I’m really sorry.

604
00:39:26,072 --> 00:39:30,493
Okay, I’m sorry that we pretended
to have a consultation.

605
00:39:31,452 --> 00:39:34,288
I just wanted to prove to Loki
that you’re innocent.

606
00:39:35,289 --> 00:39:39,210
Please, Prof,
I’m the one apologizing for Loki.

607
00:39:41,087 --> 00:39:42,463
I accept your apology.

608
00:39:43,297 --> 00:39:44,798
Though I can’t deny the fact

609
00:39:44,799 --> 00:39:48,886
that I feel disrespected
and I’m very disappointed.

610
00:39:49,011 --> 00:39:51,806
It’s like he even took my help
to the students the wrong way.

611
00:39:52,598 --> 00:39:53,724
I'm sorry, Prof.

612
00:40:43,315 --> 00:40:44,859
Morayta already left.

613
00:40:45,651 --> 00:40:47,153
That phone isn’t his.

614
00:40:48,028 --> 00:40:50,030
But we can hear the ringtone.

615
00:40:51,490 --> 00:40:52,825
Who could he be?

616
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:07,464
Hello?

617
00:41:22,897 --> 00:41:25,149
It’s a pleasure
to finally meet you in person...

618
00:41:25,566 --> 00:41:27,818
Lorelei, Loki.

619
00:41:28,903 --> 00:41:30,946
I am Moriarty.

620
00:41:47,171 --> 00:41:49,047
Don’t you believe

621
00:41:49,048 --> 00:41:52,635
that the weakling math prodigy
you helped

622
00:41:53,052 --> 00:41:54,261
is Moriarty?

623
00:41:55,387 --> 00:41:58,807
You know, if you like puzzles,
we’d get along.

624
00:41:59,683 --> 00:42:01,852
So what, are we partners?

625
00:42:04,897 --> 00:42:05,897
Okay.

626
00:42:17,868 --> 00:42:21,580
You see, money makes the world
go round.

627
00:42:21,830 --> 00:42:24,874
Why would I waste my time
doing a good cause?

628
00:42:24,875 --> 00:42:26,544
I wouldn’t get anything out of it anyway.

629
00:42:28,754 --> 00:42:30,923
Have you ever kissed that girl?

630
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:40,599
Don’t think about it too much.

631
00:42:41,809 --> 00:42:42,809
Stein!

632
00:42:45,688 --> 00:42:46,689
One more thing...
